	<string>Export Data (CSV)</string>
	<key>faq_backup_how_answer</key>
	<string>Go to Settings → Preferences → Stats &amp; Data → Export Backup. This creates a JSON file you can save to Files, iCloud Drive, or share anywhere. To restore, tap Restore Backup and select your backup file.</string>
	<key>faq_backup_how_question</key>
	<string>How do I back up my data?</string>
	<key>faq_contact_support</key>
	<string>Contact Support</string>
	<key>faq_create_event_answer</key>
	<string>Tap the + button at the bottom right of the main screen. You can create a timed Event (with a start time and duration) or a Habit (recurring daily task). Fill in the title, pick an icon and color, then tap Create.</string>
	<key>faq_create_event_question</key>
	<string>How do I create my first event?</string>
	<key>faq_customization_accent_color_a</key>
	<string>Go to Settings → Preferences → Appearance → Accent Color. Choose from the preset palette or use the color picker to set any custom color. The accent color applies to the timeline line, buttons, and highlights throughout the app.</string>
	<key>faq_customization_accent_color_q</key>
	<string>How do I change the app accent color?</string>
	<key>faq_customization_density_a</key>
	<string>Timeline Density controls how much vertical space is allocated between events. Compact fits more on screen, while Comfortable adds more breathing room. Adjust it in Settings → Preferences → Appearance.</string>
	<key>faq_customization_density_q</key>
	<string>What is Timeline Density?</string>
	<key>faq_customization_event_icon_a</key>
	<string>Nhấn vào một sự kiện để mở màn hình chi tiết. Nhấn vào icon ở phía trên để mở Icon &amp; Color picker. Bạn có thể tìm bất kỳ SF Symbol nào và chọn từ hàng trăm icon, sau đó chọn màu tùy chỉnh.</string>
	<key>faq_customization_event_icon_q</key>
	<string>How do I change an event's icon or color? </string>
	<key>faq_customization_hide_completed_a</key>
	<string>Yes. Go to Settings → Preferences → Productivity and toggle on Hide Completed Events. Completed events will be hidden from the timeline until you toggle it off again.</string>
	<key>faq_customization_hide_completed_q</key>
	<string>Can I hide completed events?</string>
	<key>faq_customization_title</key>
	<string>Customization</string>
	<key>faq_data_backup_title</key>
	<string>Data &amp; Backup</string>
	<key>faq_data_where_answer</key>
	<string>All your data is stored locally on your device. Line does not have any servers — your events, habits, and logs never leave your iPhone unless you choose to export them.</string>
	<key>faq_data_where_question</key>
	<string>Where is my data stored?</string>
	<key>faq_delete_app_answer</key>
	<string>All local data will be permanently deleted. We strongly recommend exporting a backup before uninstalling. If you have iCloud Backup enabled on your iPhone, some data may be included in your device backup.</string>
	<key>faq_delete_app_question</key>
	<string>What happens if I delete the app?</string>
	<key>faq_event_vs_habit_answer</key>
	<string>Events are one-off or recurring time blocks — like meetings, workouts, or study sessions. They have a start time and an optional duration. Habits are recurring tasks you want to build consistency with — they show a completion ring and track your streaks over time.</string>
	<key>faq_event_vs_habit_question</key>
	<string>What's the difference between an Event and a Habit?</string>
	<key>faq_export_csv_answer</key>
	<string>Yes — go to Settings → Preferences → Stats &amp; Data → Export CSV. This exports your last 90 days of events and habits with completion status into a CSV file that opens in Numbers, Excel, or Google Sheets.</string>
	<key>faq_export_csv_question</key>
	<string>Can I export my history to a spreadsheet?</string>
	<key>faq_filter_all</key>
	<string>All</string>
	<key>faq_habits_accumulative_a</key>
	<string>An accumulative habit has a numeric target — like drinking 2,000 ml of water or walking 10,000 steps. Each tap adds your increment (e.g. +250 ml). A progress ring fills as you go, completing when you hit your target.</string>
	<key>faq_habits_accumulative_q</key>
	<string>What is an Accumulative habit?</string>
	<key>faq_habits_mark_done_a</key>
	<string>Tap the circle button on the right side of any habit row. For binary habits it toggles complete/incomplete. For accumulative habits, each tap adds your set increment — keep tapping until you reach the target.</string>
	<key>faq_habits_mark_done_q</key>
	<string>How do I mark a habit as done?</string>
	<key>faq_habits_repeat_options_a</key>
	<string>You can set a habit to repeat Every Day, on Weekdays only, on specific days of the week, for a fixed range (1 week or 1 month), or just once on a single day.</string>
	<key>faq_habits_repeat_options_q</key>
	<string>What repeat options are available for habits?</string>
	<key>faq_habits_streak_a</key>
	<string>Yes — open the Stats tab (chart icon in the tab bar) to see your current streak, best streak, and a 30-day completion calendar for each habit. You can adjust the streak threshold in Settings → Preferences.</string>
	<key>faq_habits_streak_q</key>
	<string>Can I track my habit streaks?</string>
	<key>faq_habits_title</key>
	<string>Habits</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_evening_review_a</key>
	<string>Evening Review sends you a nightly reminder to reflect on your day and plan tomorrow. Set your preferred time in Settings → Preferences → Notifications → Evening Review. Premium feature.</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_evening_review_q</key>
	<string>What is Evening Review?</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_event_setup_a</key>
	<string>Go to Settings → Notifications and enable the global toggle. You can set a lead time (how many minutes before an event you're notified) and toggle notifications on or off for individual event types.</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_event_setup_q</key>
	<string>How do I set up notifications for events?</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_morning_briefing_a</key>
	<string>Morning Briefing sends you a notification each morning with a summary of your day's schedule. Set the time in Settings → Preferences → Notifications → Morning Briefing. Premium feature.</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_morning_briefing_q</key>
	<string>What is Morning Briefing?</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_not_receiving_a</key>
	<string>Make sure notifications are enabled in both Line (Settings → Notifications) and in iOS Settings → Line → Notifications. Also check that Focus modes aren't blocking the app.</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_not_receiving_q</key>
	<string>Why am I not receiving notifications?</string>
	<key>faq_notifications_title</key>
	<string>Notifications</string>
	<key>faq_premium_refund_answer</key>
	<string>Refunds are handled by Apple. Visit reportaproblem.apple.com, sign in with your Apple ID, find the Line purchase, and submit a refund request. Apple typically processes refunds within a few days.</string>
	<key>faq_premium_refund_question</key>
	<string>Can I get a refund?</string>
	<key>faq_premium_restore_answer</key>
	<string>Go to Settings → Account → Restore Purchase, or open the Premium screen and tap Restore Purchase at the bottom. As long as you're signed in with the same Apple ID, your purchase will be restored instantly.</string>
	<key>faq_premium_restore_question</key>
	<string>How do I restore my purchase on a new device?</string>
	<key>faq_premium_subscription_answer</key>
	<string>No — Line Premium is a one-time purchase of $4.99 USD. You pay once and own it forever. There are no monthly fees, no renewals, and no surprise charges.</string>
	<key>faq_premium_subscription_question</key>
	<string>Is Premium a subscription?</string>
	<key>faq_premium_title</key>
	<string>Premium</string>
	<key>faq_premium_what_answer</key>
	<string>Line Premium unlocks: unlimited events and habits (free is limited to 50 each), all accent colors, all icons, full notification features (Morning Briefing &amp; Evening Review), Backup &amp; Export, and 90-day stats history.</string>
	<key>faq_premium_what_question</key>
	<string>What do I get with Premium?</string>
	<key>faq_search_placeholder</key>
	<string>Search questions...</string>
	<key>faq_still_questions</key>
	<string>Still have questions?</string>
	<key>faq_structify_answer</key>
	<string>Line is a daily timeline and habit tracker that helps you visualize your entire day from wake to sleep. You can create timed events, build recurring habits, and see everything laid out on a single scrollable timeline — so you always know what's next.</string>
	<key>faq_structify_question</key>
	<string>What is Line?</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_gap_a</key>
	<string>When there's free time between two events, Line shows a subtle message like \"A quiet hour — worth filling\". Tap it to quickly create a new event in that gap, pre-filled with the right start time.</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_gap_q</key>
	<string>What does the gap message between events mean?</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_morning_night_a</key>
	<string>These are system events that define your day's boundaries. Morning Start is your wake time and Night Reset is your sleep time. All other events are constrained within this window. You can adjust both times in Settings → Preferences → Schedule.</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_morning_night_q</key>
	<string>What are Morning Start and Night Reset?</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_move_event_a</key>
	<string>Long press on any event until it lifts (you'll feel a haptic). Then drag it up or down to the new time slot. Release to drop it. For recurring events, you'll be asked whether to move just today or all days.</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_move_event_q</key>
	<string>How do I move an event on the timeline?</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_resize_event_a</key>
	<string>Long press an event to enter hold mode, then drag the end time (shown at the bottom of the event pill) up or down to adjust the duration. The duration preview updates in real time as you drag.</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_resize_event_q</key>
	<string>How do I resize an event?</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_title</key>
	<string>Timeline</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_view_days_a</key>
	<string>Use the week strip at the top of the screen to swipe between days. You can also tap the date header to jump to any date. Past days are shown with reduced opacity to indicate they're read-only.</string>
	<key>faq_timeline_view_days_q</key>
	<string>How do I view other days?</string>
	<key>faq_try_search</key>
	<string>Try a different search term</string>
